quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  25,53,"It is He who released the two bodies of flowing water, one sweet and fresh and the other salty and bitter, and set up an insurmountable barrier between them"
  25,54,It is He who has created human beings from water and He has granted them the ties of blood as well as marriage. Your Lord is all powerful
  25,55,"Yet they worship besides God that which can neither benefit them nor harm them. One who denies the truth is a helper [of evil] against his Lord"
  25,56,We have sent you only as a bearer of glad tidings and as a warner
  25,57,"Say, \"I do not ask you for any recompense for this except that anyone who so wishes should take the right path to his Lord"
  25,58,"Put your trust in the One who is the Ever-Living [God], who never dies, and glorify Him with His praise. He is fully aware of the sins of His servants"
  25,59,"it is He who created the heavens and the earth and all that is between them in six Days [periods], then settled Himself on the throne -- the Gracious One. Ask any informed person about Him"
  25,60,"When they are told, \"Prostrate yourselves before the Gracious One,\" they ask, \"Who is this Gracious One? Shall we prostrate ourselves before whatever you will?\" This increases their aversion"
  25,61,"Exalted is He who put constellations in the heavens, a radiant lamp and an illuminating moon"
  25,62,"it is He who has made night and day succeed each other, a sign for those who would take heed and would be grateful"
  25,63,"The true servants of the Gracious One are those who walk upon the earth with humility and when they are addressed by the ignorant ones, their response is, \"Peace"
  25,64,"and those who spend the night prostrating themselves, and standing before their Lord"
  25,65,"who say, \"Our Lord, ward off from us the punishment of Hell, for its punishment is a dreadful torment to suffer"
  25,66,"Indeed, it is an evil abode and evil dwelling-place"
  25,67,"They are those who are neither extravagant nor niggardly, but keep a balance between the two"
  25,68,"those who never invoke any other deity besides God, nor take a life which God has made sacred, except with the right to do so, nor commit adultery. Anyone who does that shall face punishment"
  25,69,he shall have his suffering doubled on the Day of Resurrection and he will abide forever in disgrace
  25,70,"except for those who repent and believe and do good deeds. God will change the evil deeds of such people into good ones: He is most forgiving and most merciful"
  25,71,He who repents and does good deeds has truly turned to God
  25,72,"And those who do not bear false witness, and when they pass by frivolity, they pass by with dignity"
  25,73,who do not turn a blind eye and a deaf ear to the signs of their Lord when they are reminded of them
  25,74,"who say, \"Lord, grant us joy in our wives and children and make us a model for the righteous"
  25,75,"These are the ones who will be rewarded with lofty mansions in Paradise, for their steadfastness. They will be received therein with greetings of welcome and salutations of peace"
  25,76,"There they shall abide forever: a blessed dwelling and a blessed resting place"
  25,77,"Say, \"What would my Lord care for you, if you do not call on Him. Because you have indeed rejected the truth and His punishment is bound to overtake you"